        "title": {
          "english": "I want to go to...",
          "arabic": "أريد الذهاب إلى..."
        },
        "text": "To express your intention to go to a place, you can use the phrase 'أريدُ الذهابَ إلى...' (Ureedu al-thahaba ila...), which means 'I want to go to...'. This is useful when you need to specify your destination.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أريدُ الذهابَ إلى المصرف.",
            "english": "I want to go to the bank.",
            "transliteration": "Ureedu al-thahaba ila al-maṣrif."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أريدُ الذهابَ إلى مكتبِ البريد.",
            "english": "I want to go to the post office.",
            "transliteration": "Ureedu al-thahaba ila maktabi al-bareed."
          }
        ]
